modules.description: This module converts IPv4 addresses to and from Cstruct.t values. It provides functions to parse an IPv4 address from the first 4 octets of a Cstruct, write an IPv4 address into a Cstruct, and handle allocation. Use cases include serializing IPv4 addresses for network transmission or parsing raw byte buffers into address values.

This module converts IPv6 addresses to and from Cstruct.t values. It provides functions to parse an IPv6 address from the first 16 bytes of a cstruct, write an IPv6 address into a cstruct, and handle allocation during serialization. Use cases include network protocol implementations that require direct memory manipulation, such as packet parsing or constructing IP headers in low-level networking code.

This module converts IP addresses to and from Cstruct.t values, handling both IPv4 and IPv6 formats. It provides functions to parse addresses from raw byte buffers and serialize them into Cstructs for network transmission. Use cases include packet parsing, constructing IP headers, and working with low-level network protocols where direct memory manipulation is required.
